        {
          "title": "Medical terminology is the language of medicine",
          "durationMinutes": 15,
          "blocks": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "text": "It may seem complex at first, but once the structure is understood, the terms become easy to interpret. Medical words are built from prefixes, suffixes, and root words."
            },
            {
              "type": "nested_bullet_list",
              "items": [
                {
                  "text": "Prefix - Beginning; modifies meaning."
                },
                {
                  "text": "Suffix - Ending; indicates condition or procedure."
                },
                {
                  "text": "Root Word - Main body part."
                },
                {
                  "text": "Meaning of the full term = meaning of each part combined."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "nested_bullet_list",
              "title": "Examples",
              "items": [
                {
                  "text": "Nephritis",
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "text": "Nephr = kidney"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "-itis = inflammation"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "Meaning: inflammation of the kidney."
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "text": "Hydronephrosis",
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "text": "Hydro = water/fluid"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "Nephr = kidney"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "-osis = abnormal condition"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "Meaning: abnormal condition of fluid accumulation in the kidney."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "id": "basic-anatomy-slide-2"
        },
